\title{Interior Point}
\date{2026-03-11}
\author{boat}
\taxon{Definition}
\import{math-lib}

\p{
If #{S} is a subset of a [Euclidean space](gtop-0004), then #{x} is an \strong{interior point} of #{S} if there exists an [open ball](gtop-000S) centered at #{x} which is completely contained in #{S}.
}
